---
---

<section id="examples">
  <div class="container">
    <div class="reveal">
      <p class="section-label">In the Wild</p>
      <h2 class="section-title">Real Projects Using Coherence</h2>
      <p class="section-desc">
        We used Coherence to build an integration plugin between OpenClaw and Injectionator —
        contributing to someone else's codebase with architectural guardrails keeping Claude in bounds.
      </p>

      <div class="examples-grid grid-2">
        <div class="example-card card">
          <div class="example-header">
            <h3>OpenClaw Plugin</h3>
            <span class="example-tag">Contributing to an external repo</span>
          </div>
          <p class="example-desc">
            OpenClaw is a multi-channel AI gateway with 33 extension plugins and strict conventions.
            We ran <code>/coherence</code> to scaffold SPEC docs that enforce plugin isolation —
            documenting boundaries around core internals, requiring the plugin SDK, and keeping extensions self-contained.
          </p>
          <div class="terminal">
            <div class="terminal-header">
              <span class="terminal-dot"></span>
              <span class="terminal-dot"></span>
              <span class="terminal-dot"></span>
              <span class="terminal-title">plugin-boundary.cjs</span>
            </div>
            <div class="terminal-body">
              <span class="comment">// PreToolUse hook — fires on every Edit/Write</span><br />
              <span class="comment">// inside extensions/</span><br /><br />
              <span class="keyword">if</span> (importsFromCore) &#123;<br />
              &nbsp;&nbsp;<span class="keyword">return</span> &#123;<br />
              &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;decision: <span class="string">"block"</span>,<br />
              &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;reason: <span class="string">"Use openclaw/plugin-sdk,<br />
              &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;not ../../src/agents/"</span><br />
              &nbsp;&nbsp;&#125;<br />
              &#125;
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="example-card card">
          <div class="example-header">
            <h3>Injectionator Integration</h3>
            <span class="example-tag">Prompt injection protection</span>
          </div>
          <p class="example-desc">
            The Injectionator scans prompts for injection attacks. We wired it into OpenClaw's
            hook pipeline at six points — covering user messages, tool responses, system prompts,
            and more. SPEC documents tracked each integration point as a falsifiable claim.
          </p>
          <div class="terminal">
            <div class="terminal-header">
              <span class="terminal-dot"></span>
              <span class="terminal-dot"></span>
              <span class="terminal-dot"></span>
              <span class="terminal-title">SPEC-HOOKS.md</span>
            </div>
            <div class="terminal-body">
              <span class="comment"># Hook Integration Points</span><br /><br />
              <span class="status-ok">CURRENT</span> &nbsp;beforeRequest hook<br />
              <span class="status-ok">CURRENT</span> &nbsp;afterResponse hook<br />
              <span class="status-ok">CURRENT</span> &nbsp;toolCall hook<br />
              <span class="status-drift">DRIFTED</span> &nbsp;systemPrompt hook<br />
              <span class="comment"># ^ Agent flags this for review</span>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <p class="example-cta">
        <a href="/blog/learning-the-happy-path">Read the full case study &rarr;</a>
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<style>
  .example-header {
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    justify-content: space-between;
    margin-bottom: 0.75rem;
  }

  .example-header h3 {
    font-size: 1.15rem;
  }

  .example-tag {
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    font-size: 0.7rem;
    color: var(--text-muted);
    background: var(--bg-surface);
    padding: 0.2em 0.6em;
    border-radius: var(--radius-sm);
    white-space: nowrap;
  }

  .example-desc {
    font-size: 0.92rem;
    color: var(--text-secondary);
    line-height: 1.55;
    margin-bottom: 1.25rem;
  }

  .example-desc code {
    font-size: 0.85em;
    background: var(--bg-surface);
    padding: 0.15em 0.4em;
    border-radius: var(--radius-sm);
  }

  .keyword {
    color: var(--cyan);
  }

  .string {
    color: var(--green);
  }

  .status-ok {
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    font-size: 0.85em;
    color: var(--green);
    font-weight: 600;
  }

  .status-drift {
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    font-size: 0.85em;
    color: var(--amber);
    font-weight: 600;
  }

  .example-cta {
    text-align: center;
    margin-top: 2rem;
  }

  .example-cta a {
    color: var(--cyan);
    font-weight: 500;
    text-decoration: none;
    border-bottom: 1px solid transparent;
    transition: border-color 0.2s;
  }

  .example-cta a:hover {
    border-bottom-color: var(--cyan);
  }
</style>
